casebody.data:
The People of the State of New York v. Florence Finkelstein.

Motion granted insofar as to enlarge appellant’s time to procure the record on appeal and appellant’s points to be served and filed to and including December 8, 1959, with notice of argument for the January 1960 Term of this court, said appeal to be argued or submitted when reached. Concur — Breitel, J. P., M. M. Frank, Valente, McNally and Stevens, JJ.
